The paper discusses a policy-based framework for end-to-end QoS management in converged networks, which involves resource management and fuzzy-based rule allocation. This work is related to network infrastructure (cs.NI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
